OL,3,GYorkshire & Humber
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FBecoming dry
OL,6,Finto the evening, with extensive low
OL,7,Fcloud very gradually thinning and
OL,8,Fdeveloping breaks overnight. Given the
OL,9,Flight winds, frost is expected in many
OL,10,Fareas, with some fog or freezing fog
OL,11,Fpatches also possible later in the
OL,12,Fnight.
OL,13,
OL,14,CSaturday:FBrightest in the north, with
OL,15,Fsome eventual sunny intervals once
OL,16,Fearly low cloud clears, as cloudier
OL,17,Fconditions periodically affect the
OL,18,Fsouth. Becoming generally cloudy with
OL,19,Fsome rain into the evening.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
